AC   Q45729;
Pesticidal crystal protein cry15Aa (Insecticidal delta-endotoxin
CryXVA(a)) (Crystaline entomocidal protoxin) (38 kDa crystal protein).
"Molecular characterization of two novel crystal protein genes from
Bacillus thuringiensis subsp. thompsoni.";
-!- FUNCTION: Promotes colloidosmotic lysis by binding to the midgut
    epithelial cells of lepidopteran larvae.
-!- DEVELOPMENTAL STAGE: The crystal protein is produced during
    sporulation and is accumulated both as an inclusion and as part of
    the spore coat.
Plasmid; Sporulation; Toxin.
